                    <comment id="12457301" author="jukkaz" created="Mon, 11 Dec 2006 11:55:34 +0000"  >Upgraded jackrabbit-core to use Derby 10.2.1.6 in revision 485605. Passes all unit tests and seems to work fine with existing repositories, so likely no manual upgrade steps are required.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
There are some improvements in the Derby 10.2 disk layout that are by default not enabled when using a database created with 10.1. To get full benefits in 10.2, one needs to include the &amp;quot;upgrade=true&amp;quot; attribute in the JDBC connection string. I&amp;#39;ll probably include a note about this in the Jackrabbit 1.2 release notes.</comment>
